job.description:
Our client is a late-stage software security unicorn currently experiencing exponential growth from an unprecedented increase in market demand. This is an opportunity to partake in an IPO and make a substantial impact on the product within a growing engineering organization.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;As a member of the Platform Engineering Team, you will design, develop, and deploy code critical to maintaining software on different platforms, bridging the gap between hardware and software.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;   Are you ready for a highly collaborative and exhilarating work environment?&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Responsibilities you will take on:&amp;nbsp;  - Design, Develop and Deploy Code (80%)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;   
  - Implement Python tooling (scripts, APIs) for the development team and the product&amp;nbsp;   
  - Use&amp;nbsp;relational and non-relational databases to&amp;nbsp;promote data flow&amp;nbsp;   
&amp;nbsp;Your Profile:&amp;nbsp;  - BS or MS (STEM Degree)    
  - 1-3+ years of&amp;nbsp;experience designing and&amp;nbsp;deploying&amp;nbsp;software&amp;nbsp;   
  - Proficiency&amp;nbsp;with modern programming languages&amp;nbsp;such as Python or&amp;nbsp;Modern C++   
  - Experience with&amp;nbsp;Unix/Linux&amp;nbsp;   
  - Comfortable&amp;nbsp;debugging, testing, and documenting&amp;nbsp;   
Nice to have:&amp;nbsp;  - Cloud computing experience (AWS, Azure,&amp;nbsp;etc)&amp;nbsp;   
  - Familiarity with&amp;nbsp;CI/CD systems&amp;nbsp;   
  - Experience with infrastructure as code, such as Terraform&amp;nbsp;   
  - Docker and/or&amp;nbsp;Podman&amp;nbsp;exposure&amp;nbsp;   
&amp;nbsp;If you are currently open to new opportunities and want to take your career to the next level, please contact me to discuss this opportunity along with alternative&amp;nbsp;Engineering&amp;nbsp;positions within the Austin Computer Software Technology Space.&amp;nbsp;All conversations are confidential, and we will only submit your information after attaining your consent.&amp;nbsp;
